RAW TEXT CLEANER
----------------
Formats raw text input and outputs file for use in 
training natural language recommendation model.

use: (base) $> python cleaner.py inputFile outputFileName 
----------------

Requres nltk which is installed in the anaconda base environment. You must activate this environment 
on the command line before running this program:

$> conda activate base
(base) $> cleaner.py inputFile outputFileName

ntlk requires punkt for tokenization. the program will attempt to download this package each time but will only install
if it isn't already present. 
